    <!-- FAQ Strings -->
    <string name="faq_title">FAQ</string>
    <string name="faq_cat_guide">Setup Guide</string>
    <string name="faq_q_add_rule">Q: How to add parser rules for my music app?</string>
    <string name="faq_a_add_rule">Follow these steps to add a rule:\n\n
1. <b>Enable App Settings</b>: Ensure features like "Notification Lyrics", "Media Notification Lyrics", or "Car Bluetooth Lyrics" are enabled in your music app.\n\n
2. <b>Add Parser Rule</b>: Go to the Parser Rules page and select "Add Music App".\n
   • Fill in the app name and package name.\n
   • If "Recommend current playing app" is enabled, click the button to auto-fill.\n\n
3. <b>Configure Parsing</b>:\n
   • Enable "Media Notification Lyrics".\n
   • Select the "Separator" and "Order" based on how the notification looks.\n\n
4. <b>Restart to Apply</b>: Save the rule, remove the music app from recents, and restart it.\n\n
<b>Note</b>: If the app lacks these features, try the SuperLyric/Lyric Getter options or "Online Lyrics" as a backup.</string>
    <string name="faq_q_super_island">Q: How to use Xiaomi Super Island notification?</string>
    <string name="faq_a_super_island">If rooted: Use HyperCeiler to bypass the whitelist.\n\nIf not rooted: Authorize this app in Shizuku and enable \'Bypass Xiaomi Super Island Whitelist\'. Note: This may increase power consumption and message delay.</string>
    <string name="faq_cat_func">Functionality Issues</string>
    <string name="faq_q_no_lyrics">Q: Why can\'t I see lyrics?</string>
    <string name="faq_a_no_lyrics">A: Please check the following steps:\n\n
1. <b>Check Permissions</b>: Ensure the app has all necessary permissions (especially Notification Access).\n\n
2. <b>Check System Version</b>:\n
   - Recommended: Android 16+ or HyperOS 3.0.300+.\n
   - Compatibility Warning: Other versions are not fully tested and may be unstable.\n
   - HyperOS Note: Versions below 3.0.300 cannot display native live notifications.\n\n
3. <b>Check Music App Settings</b>:\n
   - QQ Music/Netease/Xiaomi Music etc.: Some versions may require connecting headphones to trigger \"Car Bluetooth Lyrics\" or \"Notification Lyrics\".\n
   - Apple Music etc.: Apps relying on SuperLyric API must have the SuperLyric module installed (requires LSPosed).\n\n
4. <b>Online Lyric Limits</b>: If using online lyrics, API limitations may temporarily prevent fetching accurate lyrics.</string>

    <string name="faq_q_service_error">Q: Why does the home page say "Cannot connect to service"?</string>
    <string name="faq_a_service_error">A: This is usually because the system automatically revoked permissions.\n\n
<b>Reason</b>: Some systems limit the duration of "Notification Access" authorization.\n
<b>Solution</b>: Please go to system settings and re-grant Notification Access to this app.</string>
    
    <string name="faq_cat_feedback">Feedback &amp; Logs</string>
    <string name="faq_q_unresolved">Q: None of the above solved my problem. What should I do?</string>
    <string name="faq_a_unresolved">A: Please submit an Issue on the feedback page.   - <b>Recommended</b>: GitHub Issues (Highest efficiency).  - <b>Alternative</b>: WPS Form (May require login).   <b>Important</b>: When submitting feedback, please attach <b>Logs</b> to help us troubleshoot.</string>

    <string name="faq_q_get_log">Q: How do I get logs?</string>
    <string name="faq_a_get_log">A: It depends on your version:   - <b>Debug Version</b>: Has a built-in Log Console to view full logs directly.  - <b>Release / Pre-release Version</b>: Tap the version number or Commit hash in the app multiple times to open the Log Console.</string>


